# Harmony AI App System Patterns
@Arch: Three-Tier Mobile (Presentation → Business Logic → Data)
- Screen Components: Full-page views, navigation, screen state
- Presentational Components: Pure display, props-driven, reusable
- Container Components: Data fetching, side effects, service connection
- State: Local (useState) → Context (theme/auth/emoji) → Redux/Zustand (future complex state)
- Navigation: Stack (primary), Modal (future)
@Components:
- Screens: HomeScreen, ChatScreen, CharacterListScreen, EmojiActionEditorScreen
- Services: HarmonyLinkService (REST), WebSocketService (real-time), EmojiService, EntityEmojiActionService
- Storage: SQLite (messages/characters/interactions/emoji_actions), AsyncStorage (settings/preferences/reply mode)
- Theme: Centralized via React Native Paper, Harmony Link palette
- Sync: Optimistic updates, background sync, conflict resolution (last-write-wins)
@Database:
- SQLite with SQLCipher encryption, schema matches Harmony Link, migrations in /src/database/migrations/
- Storage Pattern: Base64-encoded binary data stored in TEXT columns (audio, images) for simpler cross-platform handling
- Transaction Pattern CRITICAL: withTransaction() helper CANNOT be used for INSERT operations returning insertId
  - Problem: React Native SQLite uses run-to-completion semantics; Promise resolution occurs AFTER transaction commits
  - Solution: Use direct transaction callbacks with Promise wrappers for INSERT operations
  - Pattern: db.transaction((tx) => { tx.executeSql(..., (_, result) => resolve(result.insertId)) })
- Safe withTransaction() uses: UPDATE/DELETE with rowsAffected checks, SELECT queries
- Unsafe withTransaction() uses: INSERT returning insertId, multiple sequential statements
- All repositories follow this pattern: providers.ts, modules.ts, characters.ts, entities.ts, conversation_messages.ts, interactions.ts, emoji_actions.ts
- Interaction Pattern: Tables prefixed with interactions_*, keyed by interaction_id, participant_key derived from sorted entity ID pairs
- Emoji Pattern: emoji_actions table with entity-level mappings, JSON emotion_effects column, soft delete via deleted_at
- JOIN Query Pattern: conversation_messages JOIN interactions for chat list previews (last message per interaction), with two-phase TEXT column loading for audio/image data
@Decisions:
- React Native CLI (not Expo): Full native control for Executorch/messengers
- React Native Paper: Material Design 3 consistency
- React Navigation: Type-safe stack navigation
- TypeScript strict: Type safety, better DX
- Hooks → Redux/Zustand: Monitor complexity, add when needed
- SQLite: Local data persistence, Harmony Link schema compatible
- Offline queue: Queue operations when offline, process when online
@Patterns:
- Service Layer: All API calls centralized
- Queue-based Offline: Detect connection → queue ops → process when online
- Optimistic UI: Update UI immediately, sync async, handle conflicts
- Virtualized Lists: FlatList for performance
- Secure Storage: EncryptedStorage for sensitive data
- Error Boundaries: Graceful error handling
@Performance: FlatList virtualization, image lazy loading/caching, memoization, clean listener management.
@Security: HTTPS only, token auth, encrypted storage, no credentials in code.
@ProviderArchitecture:
- App mirrors Harmony Link's provider config system via sync, not management API
- Provider types: openai, openaicompatible, openrouter (OpenAI family with extended params), elevenlabs, kindroid, kajiwoto, characterai, harmonyspeech (stt/vad/tts), comfyui, tts_openai, rag_*, stt_openai/vad_openai, google, xai, anthropic (15 total)
- Schema-driven forms: providerFieldSchemas.ts defines fields per provider type (no module-specific schemas — one schema per provider across all modules)
- Module-specific fields: Merged into main provider schemas with tooltips (e.g., TTS OpenAI voice/speed fields in main OpenAI schema)
- Sampling preset sync: sampling_preset_name + extra_params columns via migration 021
- Extra params stored as JSON TEXT, edited as key-value pairs in UI
- Advanced sampling params: typical_p, tfs, dry_multiplier, dry_base, dry_allowed_length, dry_sequence_breakers, xtc_probability, xtc_threshold
- Shared isProviderConfigInUse() helper with UNION ALL for existence checks (replaces 8 separate queries)
- Model field unification: single `model` column per provider config table (migration 000030)
@InteractionSession:
- Replaces DualEntitySession pattern: sessions are scoped to interaction IDs (not entity-pair IDs)
- InteractionSession interface: interactionId, interaction, participantIds, ownEntityId, connections Map (entityId → connection info), pendingTranscriptions Map
- Events keyed by interactionId: 'session:started', 'session:stopped', 'message:received', 'typing:indicator', etc.
- Participant-agnostic: supports N participants per session (world/private/group)
- Navigation adapted: ChatDetailScreen uses interactionId for session lookup instead of partnerEntityId
- Participant key derivation: private (sorted pair "entityA+entityB"), group (sorted join of all IDs), world (empty string)
- Scope derivation: 0-1 participants → world, 2 → private, 3+ → group
@EmojiArchitecture:
- Emoji Sets: native (platform default), twemoji (Twitter sprite), noto (Google sprite) — selected via EmojiContext
- Emoji Picker: Modal (full-screen, category tabs, search) and Inline (compact for chat input)
- Emoji Data: Pre-built emoji data service (EmojiService) loading from bundled data, category-based organization
- Emoji Actions: Entity-level emoji→action mappings stored in emoji_actions table
  - Action types: trigger custom emotion effects on emoji send
  - Emotion effects: Ekman8 emotion deltas (joy/sadness/trust/disgust/fear/anger/surprise/anticipation)
  - Resolution: EmojiService scans outgoing message text, resolves emoji → actions → AdditionalEffects payload → sent with SEND_MESSAGE
- Emoji-Aware Text: EmojiAwareText segments text into emoji/text spans; EmojiText renders with proper sprite caching
- DB: Migrations 22-23 via emoji_actions repository with soft delete pattern
@SessionResume:
- Session resume flow: INIT_ENTITY response includes `resumed: true` flag on Harmony Link side
- EntitySessionService checks resumed flag; if true, avoids re-creating connection and reconciles pending state
- Dangling event sync: On reconnect, backend refires any events that were queued while disconnected
- Reply mode: EntitySession passes `reply_mode` as capability during INIT_ENTITY; ChatPreferencesService stores per-partner preference
